>>WELCOME BACK TO THE FIVE METER DIVING NCAA
NATIONAL CHAMPIONSHIP.

OUR FINALISTS<em> ARE BRYAN LANCE AND JASON GRAY.

<em>FOR?
>>PERFECTION MATT.</em>

<em>WHEN YOU HAVE MADE IT THIS
FAR, EVERY MISTAKE WILL BE</em>

<em>PENALIZED BY THE JUDGES.
>>BRYAN IS GOING FIRST.

<em>YOU CAN SEE THE MAGNITUDE OF THIS MOMENT
WEIGHING ON HIM.

<em>BRIAN AND HIS COACH HAVE BEEN
WORKING ON THIS

<em>DIVE FOR A LONG TIME.
I BELIEVE THE TWO OF THEM HAVE BEEN TOGETHER

<em>SINCE BRIAN WAS SIX.
>>UH, YES, BEFORE THAT BRIAN HAD A CHILDHOOD.

[SPLASH]<em> WELL IT'S CERTAINLY
WASN'T PERFECT, BUT NOT A TERRIBLE

<em>WAY TO START.
YOU SEE HE DOES A GOOD ATTEMPT AT A FRONT ARM
<em>STAND SOMERSAULT, BUT HE DIDN'T HOLD HIS

<em>ARM STAND AS LONG AS HE SHOULD HAVE.
AND NOT TO MENTION HE SPLASHED ABOUT FIVE

<em>DROPS OF WATER,
THERE CRAIG, NOT GOING TO CUT IT.

<em>>>AS EXPECTED THE JUDGES WERE NOT IMPRESSED.
*DECENT, BUT IS IT GOOD ENOUGH TO WIN?

<em>>>AND HERE GOES JASON GRAY.
*NOT THE FAVORITE BUT DEFINITELY A STRONG

<em>CHALLENGER.
OH AND THERE GOES THE TOWEL.

<em>HE'S USED IT AS A GRENADE.</em>
[SPLASH] >> <em>THAT WAS AMAZING.

<em>>>THAT WAS LIKE WATCHING AN ANGEL GLIDE INTO
A POOL OF COOL WHIP.

[CHEERS] <em>>>FANTASTIC SCORES CRAIG.
>>BRYAN SEEMS TO BE CONFUSED WITH HOW HE'S

<em>GOING TO COMPETE WITH THE
FLAWLESSNESS THAT IS JASON GRAY.

<em>>>WELL THERE ARE STILL FIVE
DIVES TO GO THERE, CRAIG.

♪♪
[SPLASH]

<em>>>BRIAN'S BACKWARD ROTATION,
I'VE SEEN BETTER.

<em>>>JASON GRAY ATTEMPTING THE CANNON BALL.</em>
[SPLASH] <em>I HAVE NEVER SEEN BETTER!

[CHEERS] [SPLASH]
<em>>>A LOT OF FLIPS.

<em>A LOT OF FLIPS.
>>NOT ONE FOR VARIETY THERE.

<em>>>NO.
OH, THE FLOATY!

<em>I HAVEN'T SEEN THAT USED SINCE '86.
>>PERFECT CALL BACK.

<em>>HM.
>>[SIGH] >>OH THE PIRATE

<eM>WALKING THE PLANK!
>>BRINGS TEARS TO MY EYES, THIS HOWEVER BRINGS

<em>YAWNS TO MY MOUTH.
>>INDEED.

<em>WHAT DOES HE HAVE THIS TIME?
>>OH-OH!

<em>HE'S ATTEMPTING THE WRIGGLE.
>>OH WE ARE ALL WITNESSES!

[CHEERS] <em>FLAWLESS ENTRY.
WELL THIS LAST DIVE IS JUST A FORMALITY FOR

<em>JASON GRAY.
HE IS SO FAR AHEAD IN POINTS HE CAN LITERALLY

<em>DO NO WRONG.
>>UNLESS HE TRIES A BACK ONE AND A HALF

<em>SOMERSAULT HALF TWIST
LIKE THAT FOOL BRYAN LANCE.

[LAUGHTER] >>GOOD POINT,
BUT IS ANYONE THAT STUPID?

>>OH, UH- SORRY TO CUT YOU OFF CRAIG,
BUT WE HAVE JUST HEARD <em>THAT JASON GRAY IS
<em>GOING TO ATTEMPT THE BELLY FLOP.

<em>>>FROM THAT HEIGHT?
THAT'S SUICIDE.

>>YES IT IS.
<em>BUT IF HE PULLS IT OFF, HIS COLLEGIATE LEGACY

<em>WILL BE COMPLETE.
>>I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN WATCH THIS SHANNON.

<em>>>YOU HAVE TO CRAIG.
YOU'RE COMMENTATING.

<em>>>OH YEAH.
>>HE LOOKS LIKE HE'S GOING THROUGH WITH IT.
<em>>>SHAKING IT OFF.

<em>OH, PERFECT APPROACH.
THE CROWD HOLDS THEIR BREATH.
[SPLASH]

<em>>>IS HE ALIVE?
>>THE BELLY FLOP.
THE MOST RESPECTED <em>AND FEARED DIVE OF ALL TIME.
<em>HAS TAKEN A NATIONAL TREASURE.

<em>>>WAIT. WAIT!
I SEE HIM MOVING!

<em>HE'S ALIVE!
MICHAEL PHELPS MOVE OVER, THERE IS A NEW

KING OF THE POOL!
[CHEERING] <em>>>OH MY BOTOX IS

<em>ALMOST LETTING ME CRY!
[LAUGHTER]<em> >>THERE HE IS, JASON GRAY

<em>THE NEW NCAA FIVE METER DIVING CHAMPION!
STAY TUNED FOR WOMEN'S BOWLING.
